==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydrastine
<hw>Hy*dras"tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An alkaloid, found in the rootstock of the golden seal
(<spn>Hydrastis Canadensis</spn>), and extracted as a bitter, white,
crystalline substance. It is used as a tonic and febrifuge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydra-tainted</ent>⟦br⟧
